title: Kate Middleton and Prince William met Jackie Chan during Chinese President’s visit to the U.K.
text:
Tweet 
William and Kate met Hong Kong actor Jackie Chan when they stepped out for their second day of engagements with Chinese President Xi Jinping and his wife, Madame Peng Liyuan. 
The Duke and Duchess of Cambridge, both 33, attended the “Creative Collaborations” exhibition at Lancaster House on Wednesday, October 21, in London, and the royal parents-of-two were joined by Chinese President, his wife and actor/martial arts legend Jackie Chan. 
Kate Middleton looked ravishing in a Dolce & Gabbana plum lace dress, accessorized with Gianvito Rossi shoes of the same color. 
The Royal Family Channel shared a video of Kate and William’s visit with the Chinese President and his wife, as they were taking photos with the Hong Kong actor. 
Kensington Palace also published some pictures from the event on their official Twitter page. HRH presents President Xi with @BAFTA gift to celebrate #UKChina collaboration- Jackie Chan made an appearance too! pic.twitter.com/S6vSICJNdX 
— Kensington Palace (@KensingtonRoyal) October 21, 2015 
On the evening before, Duchess Kate attended her first state banquet where she dazzled in a red Jenny Packham dress, accessorized with a Lotus Flower tiara. The royal mother-of-two also wore Queen Elizabeth II’s wedding bracelet designed by Prince Philip. 
Kate will most likely steal the show at the world premiere of the latest James Bond movie, on Oct 26, where she will be joined by her husband Prince William and her brother-in-law Prince Harry. Spread the rumor
